"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":5,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":903240,"status":"ok","timestamp":1780593218916,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"},"user_tz":-330},"id":"XibYmJKx0o7p","outputId":"b56d2927-23f8-4437-dcc3-1c18b9559274"},"outputs":[{"metadata":{"tags":null},"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Downloading dataset...\n"]},{"metadata":{"tags":null},"name":"stderr","output_type":"stream","text":["Downloading: 84.1MB [00:01, 48.2MB/s]                            \n"]},{"metadata":{"tags":null},"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Preparing to extract (reading archive structure)...\n","Extracting archive...\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["Extracting files:   0%|          | 0/100019 [00:00<?, ?file/s]/tmp/ipykernel_17795/2616086357.py:28: DeprecationWarning: Python 3.14 will, by default, filter extracted tar archives and reject files or modify their metadata. Use the filter argument to control this behavior.\n","  tar.extractall(members=tqdm(members, desc=\"Extracting files\", unit=\"file\"))\n","Extracting files: 100%|██████████| 100019/100019 [36:21<00:00, 45.86file/s]"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Extraction complete!\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["\n"]}],"source":["import urllib.request\n","import tarfile\n","from tqdm import tqdm\n","\n","url = 'http://ai.stanford.edu/~amaas/data/sentiment/aclImdb_v1.tar.gz'\n","target_path = 'aclImdb_v1.tar.gz'\n","\n","# 1. Setup a custom hook to link urllib's download progress with tqdm\n","class DownloadProgressBar(tqdm):\n","    def update_to(self, b=1, bsize=1, tsize=None):\n","        if tsize is not None:\n","            self.total = tsize\n","        self.update(b * bsize - self.n)\n","\n","# Download the archive\n","print(\"Downloading dataset...\")\n","with DownloadProgressBar(unit='B', unit_scale=True, miniters=1, desc=\"Downloading\") as t:\n","    urllib.request.urlretrieve(url, target_path, reporthook=t.update_to)\n","\n","# 2. Extract the archive\n","print(\"\\nPreparing to extract (reading archive structure)...\")\n","with tarfile.open(target_path, 'r:gz') as tar:\n","    # We first get all the files in the archive so tqdm knows the total count\n","    members = tar.getmembers()\n","\n","    # We wrap the members list in tqdm() and pass it directly to extractall()\n","    print(\"Extracting archive...\")\n","    tar.extractall(members=tqdm(members, desc=\"Extracting files\", unit=\"file\"))\n","\n","print(\"\\nExtraction complete!\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"gniJ3qKV0o7r"},"source":["### **Step 2: Preprocessing the Movie Dataset**\n","\n","To work with the data efficiently, the individual text documents are assembled into a single CSV file. The following code iterates through the extracted `train` and `test` directories, reads the positive (`pos`) and negative (`neg`) reviews, and appends them to a pandas DataFrame.\n","\n","*Note: This process can take up to 10 minutes. The `pyprind` library is used to visualize the progress.*"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":6,"metadata":{"id":"IJPE-l5E0o7s","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780594483308,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":290907,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"32a366a4-2920-4d07-b04c-d691760e1f14"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Processing movie reviews: 100%|██████████| 50000/50000 [18:19<00:00, 45.49it/s] \n"]}],"source":["import pandas as pd\n","import os\n","import sys\n","from tqdm import tqdm # Import tqdm for visual progress\n","\n","# Change the 'basepath' to the directory of the unzipped movie dataset\n","basepath = 'aclImdb'\n","labels = {'pos': 1, 'neg': 0}\n","\n","# Use tqdm for a clear visual progress bar\n","pbar = tqdm(total=50000, desc=\"Processing movie reviews\", file=sys.stdout)\n","\n","# Use a list to collect data and create DataFrame once at the end\n","data = []\n","\n","for s in ('test', 'train'):\n","    for l in ('pos', 'neg'):\n","        path = os.path.join(basepath, s, l)\n","        for file in sorted(os.listdir(path)):\n","            with open(os.path.join(path, file), 'r', encoding='utf-8') as infile:\n","                txt = infile.read()\n","            data.append([txt, labels[l]])\n","            pbar.update(1) # Update the tqdm progress bar\n","\n","pbar.close() # Close the progress bar once done\n","\n","df = pd.DataFrame(data, columns=['review', 'sentiment'])"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"0chJ8Ce20o7s"},"source":["### **Step 3: Shuffling and Saving the Data**\n","\n","Because the class labels in the assembled dataset are currently sorted, the next step is to shuffle the DataFrame using `numpy`. This is crucial for properly splitting the data into training and testing sets later. Finally, the shuffled data is exported to a CSV file."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":7,"metadata":{"id":"nFI1mC6C0o7t","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780594631016,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":2618,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}},"outputs":[],"source":["import numpy as np\n","\n","np.random.seed(0)\n","# Shuffle the DataFrame\n","df = df.reindex(np.random.permutation(df.index))\n","\n","# Save the assembled and shuffled data as a CSV\n","df.to_csv('movie_data.csv', index=False, encoding='utf-8')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"rMJqNzeg0o7t"},"source":["### **Step 4: Sanity Check**\n","\n","To confirm the data was saved correctly, you can read it back into a DataFrame and print the first few rows."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":8,"metadata":{"id":"nvmdGLY60o7v","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":143},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780594639921,"user_t